If you see a little yellow circular sticker on a price tag at Costco, it means something special to employees doing inventory. It’s not like price codes where 00 and 88 are clearance and 97 is a manager markdown. It’s meant to tell employees to weigh the items for inventory and not just count them. It is a code, just not for you. 😂
